### 9. SRv6 Path Verification
**Presenter:** Feng Yang
* **Slides:** [SRv6 Path Verification](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-spring-srv6-path-verification-00)
* **Presentation Summary:**
  This draft addresses scenarios where packets are forwarded through unexpected paths due to configuration errors or malicious injection. It proposes a hop-by-hop verification mechanism using a new Segment Routing Header (SRH) TLV containing an authentication tag and sequence numbers to prevent replay attacks. Two algorithms, HMAC-SHA and AES-CMAC, were proposed and evaluated for line-rate hardware support.
* **Discussion:**
  * The presenter requested feedback from the working group regarding router hardware compatibility and performance for the proposed algorithms.

