## Next Steps

* **`draft-ietf-spring-sr-redundancy-protection`**: Authors will publish version 09 addressing the Routing Directorate review comments regarding double SID arguments. The chairs will coordinate a new WGLC thereafter.
* **`draft-ietf-spring-sr-policy-nrp`**: Discussion on the architectural placement of the NRP selector ID (candidate path level vs. policy-level attribute) will continue on the mailing list.
* **Multipath Traffic Engineering**: The draft will remain on hold for adoption in SPRING until the base architecture progresses within the TEAS Working Group.
* **SRv6 for PPPoE Transport**: The authors will address technical comments regarding EtherType processing and the BBF coordination on the mailing list, and will update the draft to remove legacy SID format definitions.